Wash and dry produce. Halve @mandarin orange{1}. Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Add @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} and juice from mandarin to pan with chicken. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce has thickened and chicken is glazed and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Remove pan from heat and let cool slightly.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, toss @crunchy sesame salad kit{12%ounce} with included dressing and crispy toppings.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with chicken and serve.

> Four ingredients, and ten minutes: That's all you need to make this delicious dinner. Chicken breast strips are browned, then simmered with spicy-sweet Thai chili sauce and mandarin orange juice until sticky. It's all served over a salad that's tossed with crunchy toppings and a nutty sesame dressing. Now that's a dinner dream come true!